em>risk=C2=A0</em>to quote you that price: They wanted to be your counterpa=
rty on the derivative, or to buy the bonds from=C2=A0you for their own acco=
unt. Now, banks in general have less capacity to take those risks, and if y=
ou call your eight banks some of them will refuse to quote=C2=A0you a price=
, or will quote you a price that is not very attractive. And you will be ag=
grieved. =E2=80=9CWe are seeing customer service deteriorating,=E2=80=9D no=
t in the sense that Deutsche Bank doesn=E2=80=99t give its institutional cu=
stomers a snazzy app that rains confetti when they do a trade =E2=80=94=C2=
=A0the institutional customers don=E2=80=99t want that! =E2=80=94=C2=A0but =
in the sense that Deutsche Bank doesn=E2=80=99t give its institutional cust=
omers aggressive, or any, quotes on some of the trades that they want to do=
.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Meanwhile Citadel Securities really=
 is in the business of taking trading risk, and it can hire risk-takers who=
