particular cyberpunk aesthetic. And he runs a car company, so he had that c=
ompany build the car to match what he thinks Mars traffic=C2=A0should look =
like. Also I guess everyone on Mars will share his DNA? Again an=C2=A0<em>i=
diosyncratic=C2=A0</em>vision of a sci-fi future, but at least it is authen=
tically his.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">As a financial columnist and e=
verything-is-securities-fraud guy, I suppose I could ask questions like =E2=
=80=9Cif you are a Tesla shareholder, how should you feel about the fact th=
at the company=E2=80=99s chief executive officer is pushing some weird truc=
k design not because it makes economic sense but because it matches the pic=
tures in his head of what life on Mars will be like?=E2=80=9D But I don=E2=
=80=99t really care; if you=E2=80=99re a Tesla shareholder you signed up fo=
r all of this. So far the pictures in the guy=E2=80=99s head have mostly wo=
rked out for his investors.=C2=A0</p><table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%"=
